<!--
  Fides ServiceNow spoke — update-set SKELETON
  ============================================
  This is a hand-authored, human-readable skeleton (not a machine export) of the
  records that make up the Fides spoke. It documents the exact tables/fields an
  admin needs; import it via "Retrieved Update Sets → Import Update Set from XML",
  then preview + commit. Fill the <script> bodies from the sibling files:

    - x_fides Script Include  <- docs/servicenow/scripted-rest/FidesWebhookVerifier.js
    - Scripted REST resource  <- docs/servicenow/scripted-rest/fides_inbound_resource.js

  On a real ServiceNow export these <script> fields are XML-escaped inside a
  <payload> CDATA; here they are shown inline for readability. Covers:
    #229  inbound HMAC verification (Script Include + Scripted REST API)
    #232  the spoke connection alias the Flow Designer actions bind to
  The three Flow Designer actions (#232) are authored in Action Designer per
  docs/servicenow/flow-designer-actions.md; their sys_hub_action_type_definition
  records are environment-specific and are not templated here.
-->
